\">IsRankLeOne</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Valuation/ValuativeRel/Basic.html#ValuativeRel.IsRankLeOne.mk","kind":"ctor","line":980,"name":"ValuativeRel.IsRankLeOne.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/Valuation/ValuativeRel/Basic.lean#L980-L980"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">class</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Valuation/ValuativeRel/Basic.html#ValuativeRel.IsRankLeOne\"><span class=\"name\">ValuativeRel</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsRankLeOne</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Valuation/ValuativeRel/Basic.html#ValuativeRel\">ValuativeRel</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We say that a ring with a valuative relation is of rank one if\nthere exists a strictly monotone embedding of the \"canonical\" value group-with-zero into\nthe nonnegative reals, and the image of this embedding contains some element different\nfrom `0` and `1`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Valuation/ValuativeRel/Basic.html#ValuativeRel.IsRankLeOne","kind":"class","line":976,"name":"ValuativeRel.IsRankLeOne","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathl